						               													<description>Educational game developed for &amp;quot;Libera&amp;quot; an anti-mafia association that wanted a game to educate people on which bar in Perugia city, Italy, were free from slot machines.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game a player is a gambler who is wasting all the money of his family gambling on slot machines of the city's pubs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The other players cooperate all together moving family pawns in order to find him and sae his soul and the money of the family.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Twenty-five  3D Slot machines are placed in a 5x5 grid representing the city.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The gambler takes turns hiding the gameboard with a screen, and moving  his pawn of one space. The pawn is always hidden inside a 3D slot machine. Each time he moves the pawn, he leaves one hidden gold coin below the visited slot machine.&amp;#10;On the family's turn, players cooperate choosing which family pawns to activate. &amp;#10;Family pawns stay among the 3D slot machines, on the intersections of the grid.&amp;#10; When activated, a family pawn may move one space OR search in a bar in the surroundings. &amp;#10;If searching, players can look below the chosen slot machine:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    if they find the Gambler pawn, they win&amp;#10;    if they find a Gold coin, they remove the 3D slot machine from the gameboard (several gold coins may indicate the current position of the gambler)&amp;#10;    if they find nothing, they must put back the slot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The gambler wins if he runs out of gold coins without being found.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
